cs.SI, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.DL

This paper deals with the analysis of censorship mechanisms in Chinese microblogging sites, which involves natural language processing techniques and data analysis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper also involves the analysis of topics that are more likely to be censored, which falls under the category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also deals with the use of keyword-based censorship, which could be categorized under cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper involves data analysis techniques, which could be categorized under cs.DL (Machine Learning).
